D.q[6336] = "I\'m going to put that into practice right away. I need a volunteer to tame the Whitish Fangs.\nNo! Not you. I\'ve had enough of seeing you round here, and besides, the Whitish Fangs could swallow you whole before you so much as house train them. You may leave.";
D.q[4726] = "";
D.q[6853] = "";
D.q[3658] = "I\'m hungry.";
D.q[3721] = "I\'m going to turn into a bloody bucket myself if I keep on carrying all this water!";
D.q[6854] = "";
D.q[3377] = "I\'m impressed but it\'s not over yet. Here is the key that will lead you to your next fight.";
D.q[7185] = "";
D.q[5550] = "It\'s frightening what they give you in this prison. I\'d rather eat Shin Larva vomit... in fact I\'ve and it was a lot tastier. Did Brakmar hire a Bwork for a cook?\nDon\'t just sit there, do some cleaning... look, grab that broom over there and get this bloody prison cleaned up.";
D.q[6855] = "";
D.q[7195] = "";
D.q[4728] = "";
D.q[4747] = "I haven\'t got any left, the entrance to my cellar is blocked by rocks. If you can get into the cellar, you can help yourself. I\'ll give you the map and the instructions.";
D.q[6856] = "";
D.q[7196] = "";
D.q[5778] = "Now you know what\'s what, You\'re ready to play. So you\'ll need two teams of five players and one victim to play the Gobball. Failing this, a summoned Gobball will do the trick. \nBy the way, the rules I\'ve explained to you aren\'t exactly written in stone... there\'s no such thing as the Amaknan Gobball Federation or anything! Decide among yourselves, and enjoy the game!";
D.q[4850] = "Are you bringing me something?";
D.q[6857] = "";
D.q[7198] = "";
D.q[5675] = "Greetings. Did you show the renegades what\'s what?";
D.q[7197] = "";
D.q[7199] = "";
D.q[7200] = "";
D.q[7201] = "";
D.q[4084] = "Ahem, according to your constitution, I can tell that I\'ll need a Great Coralator relic to prepare your potion. Once ground to powder, I\'ll be able to withdraw all the magic power I need from it.";
D.q[6246] = "Ah, here\'s the sheet of paper. Now let\'s get that combination...\nAh seriously though, who do you take me for, some kind of Bontarian? Did you really think I was just going to hand over the jewel like that because you come here making some noise? Since it\'s Oto Mustam who\'s asking, I\'ll make you a new jewel, though. I\'ll make a list of all the materials you need for you to bring to your boss.";
D.q[7552] = "Me? I was sent here by Grandapan in person.\nIt\'s sad but a strange illness has struck the village of Pandala. The variety of drinks on the island is threatened as more and more Pandawas will not drink more than a single drink in one sitting. After a lengthy investigation, we discovered that this illness appeared a few weeks after the erection of the statue, which caused the goddess to explode with rage. That explains my presence here.\nAnyway, since you just arrived, I advise you be careful and if you discover anything that could be related to the strange illness which I\'ve just mentioned, let me know.";
D.q[4798] = "";
D.q[4803] = "Ture Inge is finding it very difficult to make Gnirreh talk. I hope he\'s able to before the trial begins.";
D.q[7501] = "";
D.q[2806] = "I see... We are indebted to the wise Lenald. I\'m going to take you to the Master.";
D.q[5149] = "";
D.q[2038] = "I\'m impressed, very impressed. The old Enutrof was wise to keep his secrets close to his chest... It was some stroke of luck you finding that combination... Would you be interested in combining your luck and my intelligence?\nThe second cave mentioned in this book is south of the Zaap of Amakna. Try to have a look inside!";
D.q[5762] = "Has Milone Corichel prepared a present for my mother?";
D.q[1947] = "*Sigh* Believe me or not, I don\'t water the lager down because I\'m stingy. I just have no choice. I have less and less beer in stock and I\'m still waiting for the next delivery. No beer means no customers, and with no customers, the tavern will close down, which means no more Tek. *sigh*";
D.q[4463] = "Another Brakmarian no-hoper? You want to take me on too?";
D.q[5011] = "This judge again? And you say you know people in high places? I\'ll think about it.";
D.q[5152] = "";
D.q[4822] = "";
D.q[7203] = "";
D.q[7502] = "";
D.q[4345] = "Hello, Bontarian friend!";
D.q[4384] = "Amayiro sent you to find the jewel? That\'s very strange, a Xelor just came with a letter telling me to give it to the next customer. Well, here you go, take the jewel.";
D.q[7204] = "";
D.q[5148] = "";
D.q[627] = "Ah! Boff Chalon sent you, very well. I\'ll teach you the basics of alchemy.\nThe basic ingredients of alchemy are flowers such as clover, linseed, orchid... Look around you wherever you are when you travel and gradually collect a varied bouquet.";
D.q[5120] = "As\'Ruoy\'Dnim didn\'t increase the effort as I asked. All the same, there\'s a lot more blood and carnage than before, so I\'m happy, I\'m getting used to it!";
D.q[7503] = "";
D.q[4564] = "Are you off your trolley? Not here, that would be madness. You want to make people suspicious of the Grandapan or what? All the same I did tell Xephires that I\'d get in touch with him to sort out the time and place of the meeting.\nI hope for your sake that they\'re all inside. I can\'t be sure as long as Grandapan is watching us, but if some is missing, Xephires will know about it!";
D.q[4645] = "Ah, a Brakmarian ally. These bloody archers really got me... quick, we have to get back to Brakmar before they catch up with us.";
D.q[7205] = "";
D.q[4761] = "Thanks a lot. I\'ll read these letters later *hic*. I\'ll give you some more time for your investigation. Don\'t *hic* worry.";
D.q[4379] = "Don\'t stay here. Go back and see your chief.";
D.q[3827] = "Hey, I remember you. You already came here, right? You got your reward buddy, I got nothing else for you. This booty\'s for the novices who still need the practice.";
D.q[2713] = "And all those adventurers infesting our island will soon be sick with the McSheth!... Huh? We have visitors?! A new Pandikaze recruit it seems...";
D.q[7206] = "";
D.q[2087] = "Bloody Enutrofs! It\'s hard to believe we\'re actually helping them in their research... Well, we have quite a situation here, don\'t we - they stay underground so long that they get sick. And then who do you think they give their germs to when they come out?! Our Tofus, of course! I don\'t know how to cure a damned Enutrof cold... Ahh, my poor Tofus... Thank the gods the Eniripsas are here...";
D.q[5089] = "Bonta really is an exciting city. You can find all sorts of little jobs that the so-called defenders refuse because they\'re too scandalous. They\'re a bunch of hypocrites if you ask me.";
D.q[5296] = "";
D.q[7207] = "";
D.q[5297] = "";
D.q[4723] = "Bring this iron to Mulic quick, I\'ll have enough trouble \'convincing\' him to reforge cursed iron.";
D.q[2942] = "I\'m impressed. Adventurers hardly ever stand up to my headbutts. As a reward, I give you my pet, this adorable black Bow Wow.";
D.q[5781] = "Glory to Djaul and to Rushu, his master!";
D.q[7208] = "";
D.q[2903] = "Excellent! You\'re now a Gokwa!";
D.q[7549] = "An excellent fight, but I think you\'re capable of facing a more formidable opponent. Go to the next platform and defeat the enemy you find there.";
D.q[7550] = "";
D.q[7209] = "";
D.q[3318] = "I\'m looking for big, aggressive Dragoturkeys to knock over the Bontarian rank and file.";
D.q[3669] = "I\'m joking. Zaaps were created by Xelor himself... to help us serve him faster! As Xelor says \'All good things come to those in haste!\' These portals are fed by the energy given off by Kamas, but some of the greedy little things eat too much and get fat. Fat and lazy cosmic portals, can you imagine that? When they get lazy, they fall asleep... then they\'re useless. It\'s my job to wake them up again. How do I do this? A short, sharp shock with a hammer, my friend. That usually sorts them out";
D.q[7210] = "";
D.q[3024] = "Hello there, stranger. Did you know that the Infinite and the Void join at the exact spot you\'re standing, if these figures are to be believed? It doesn\'t look that way at first glance, does it! Did Nistracolamus send you?";
D.q[7211] = "";
D.q[6581] = "Hello. How is the search for a decent tactician going? We have to improve the efficiency of our militia on the ground.";
D.q[5783] = "Grrroar!";
D.q[7212] = "";
D.q[6084] = "I\'m not fooled by Djaul\'s scheme, as before he\'s trying to pass Jiva off for something she\'s not.";
D.q[1840] = "Hey! Wipe that grin off your face... the end of the world is coming... Gods are enraged! We\'ve uncovered... things from the past... We\'re damned! All of us! Finished!\nMust build a shelter... get underground! Explosions are on their way. Help me... or you\'ll die too!";
D.q[1071] = "I\'m on patrol, you\'re bothering me. Get outta here!";
D.q[4446] = "Hm, how can I explain... My spies were seen and eaten by Whitish Fang guard dogs belonging to the Bonta militia. \nWe have to take the target out. You know what I\'m talking about, right?";
D.q[7213] = "";
D.q[6292] = "By Djaul, I\'m almost disappointed. If you continue being so dishonest, you might get yourself promoted. Watch out!";
D.q[6071] = "This Assemble would be a complete waste of time if it wasn\'t for the false accusations against me.";
D.q[4494] = "I\'m afraid this defeat will incite the Brakmarians to launch an offensive. We have to find a solution. Don\'t blame yourself, the enemy\'s equipment made all the difference.";
D.q[1227] = "I\'ve never seen blood like it... It\'s been genetically modified... a lot.\nAnyway, here is my analysis, as you requested.";
D.q[589] = "If you dawdle on the way, you could end up in a stew. I\'ve no doubt that a foodstuff as skilled as you would be too difficult for my worshippers to chew and digest, and it wouldn\'t be fair on them if I were to put them through it. That said, if we didn\'t have a decent amount of tender meat stocked up, I\'d think about it! Anyway, I can help you leave the village very quickly, if that\'s what you want. Whatever the case, goodbye!";
D.q[3704] = "I\'m protecting the last Elm of Incarnam. No one can cut it down. The one who dares to try will be attacked by a protector... or even by Sadida himself!";
D.q[4495] = "Justfa Lafs came to see me. He was beside himself. We have to resolve the problem of our militia\'s equipment right away. I want you to find the smith who makes this equipment and put him to the test. We have to find out who\'s responsible for such low quality. Start by asking Kosuke Ichazum... I doubt it that he\'s been doing such low-standard work. \nFor the test, I want you to ask him to make a weapon with the following resources: 10 Maple Wood, 2 Ash Wood and 1 Pyrute.";
D.q[4265] = "So? Did you find anything of interest?";
D.q[4355] = "Ecaflip travellers? Nope, haven\'t seen any recently. Although I just employed a pretty young Ecaflip, if you\'re interested in that.\nYou\'re on the job? Well, another time then, I wouldn\'t want to cross Amayiro...";
D.q[3636] = "Holy mother of... what in the hell are those guards doing? You! Yeah, you.... Go make sure those pathetic slimebags are still alive! If they are, slap them round a bit for me. We\'re at war with Rushu, son... He could be attacking us right now!";
D.q[7157] = "";
D.q[471] = "Molning to you, stlangel... It\'s good to see a walm face... Since those damn wabbits allived, they blought nothing but tellol and callots to oul small island.\nA few yeals ago, we wele living on peace and love alone. Then these monstels popped out of the glound like lutting moles... It\'s been tellible... Wolse, those cowalds only attack in gangs, alone they ale nothing.\n\nBut god Lenald told me lecently that a gloup of gallant helos would come to save us...";
D.q[7158] = "";
D.q[6230] = "A Sram? No, I haven\'t seen a Sram around here. I did see one when I was captured though.";
D.q[5035] = "A Dreggon symbol? Is this the best you could find?\nHmm, you could have tried harder, no?\nWell too bad, I\'ll just have to make do with this.";
D.q[5022] = "A letter for me? Thank you.\n*Reads it carefully, them blushes*\nMy tabi, non... I\'ll do anything to keep him from getting hurt.";
D.q[3577] = "Not bad, not bad at all... You\'re almost as courageous as I am. Okay, here you go, a little bonus.";
D.q[4315] = "A message from Oto? Thieves who are going to steal into my house? Ah! I can hear footsteps!";
D.q[4272] = "An important Bontarian? You won\'t find that kind of information around here, let me tell you!";
D.q[5922] = "A nasty aura and a twisted spirit, who else could it be but you? Did you manage to get a confession from a Bontarian spy?";
D.q[5530] = "A delay in the treason case? Hmm, hmmm... *hic*\nI hate investigations that drag on, but since you seem like a decent girl, I\'ll do what you *hic* ask in exchange for a little favour from you.\nI need alcohol to make the prisoners talk but the reserves have run out. *hic* I need a barrel of Shambrosia to continue with the questioning, only Gordo McRamsay in Amakna knows the secret. Oh, and while you\'re here, I\'m looking for an Astrub woman too, but marriage agencies aren\'t what they used to be. It would be great if you could handle it instead. Unless you\'re looking for a husband, of course, and then you won\'t have to *hic* look very far.";
D.q[3851] = "I\'m resting my tired old bones. You wouldn\'t believe all the adventures I\'ve had. Hunting Gobballs, tracking Bworks, I sailed the Seven Seas, survived a dose of Maloria, challenged Dark Vlad and...";
D.q[5374] = "So? Did you find what you were looking for?";
D.q[6428] = "And what about the others? Well if they don\'t go making trouble and pay their check, there\'ll be no problem. These are all experienced fellows, mind you... nothing like what you find in the Feubuk Inn.";
D.q[1984] = "Thanks a million! The missing ingredient is a rare flower. It\'s all white, I think you can find it east of here. When you find it, please bring it to Dragonsly the alchemist!";
D.q[2500] = "Don\'t even think you can talk to a Pandawa if you haven\'t paid the McSheth levy.";
D.q[3240] = "The wise men of this World say that this Dreggon invasion was just a divine punishment. Since Dreggons were already trapped in the sanctuary of this island, all Osamodas did was free them. It\'s said that the inhabitants of the village had forgotten what their ancestors had done to the Dreggons and that their village had been built on the Dreggon Sanctuary to conceal its existence as if they had wanted to hide to the god Osamodas their wrongdoings and their madness.";
D.q[7506] = "";
D.q[4994] = "No medallion, no help!";
D.q[3737] = "Even harvesters can craft some basic items. It gives them a bit of experience in their profession.";
D.q[2555] = "There\'s a secret meeting being held in Aerdala this very minute. We\'ve no idea what\'s going on over there... What we do know is that it has something to do with the Dofus...";
D.q[5870] = "Greetings. The air around you is dripping with evil. That\'s great! Have you got a particular reason for being here?";
D.q[3639] = "This is my two-handed shovel. There are many like it, but this one is mine. My shovel is my best friend. It\'s my life. I must master it as I must master my life. My shovel without me is useless. Without my shovel, I\'m useless. I must use my shovel true. I must aim straighter than my enemy who is aiming at me.. I must get him before he gets me. I\'ll... My shovel and myself are the defenders of Amakna. We are the masters of our enemy. We are the saviours of my life.";
D.q[6119] = "Greetings. It\'s a goood thing the Assembly didn\'t end in a bloodbath. I\'m waiting for you report.";
D.q[5569] = "Greetings. Have you found Erzal\'s Blessing?";
D.q[5176] = "Greetings. Did you get the artefact back?";
D.q[5838] = "Greetings. Don\'t worry, you\'re not disturbing me at all. What can I do for you?";
D.q[5261] = "Very well. We\'ll have a good advantage if we manage to gain control of these territories, all the Zaaps will be ours.";
D.q[6309] = "Excellent work. Thanks to you and that imbecile Xephires I\'ll soon be very rich. Take this purse of money and this food - there\'s no need to thank me, I\'ll be making enough money off you, don\'t worry. Hahaha. As for Xephires, he\'d better find out which of the convoys are the good ones. I don\'t want to end up with mountains of potatoes on my hands.";
D.q[5593] = "Good day to you, fellow Brakmarian. These Bontarians are driving me crazy with their Utopian babble.";
D.q[36] = "Woohoo! I\'m so pleased someone\'s come to visit me! It\'s not often I\'ve company in this part of Amakna. In fact, I\'m so pleased, I\'ll answer your questions, no matter how stupid they are.";
D.q[5846] = "Good day, loyal subject! Long live Allister, long live our great sovereign! May the king live a very long time.";
D.q[5942] = "I\'m sick of being interrupted all the time. People have no respect anymore. What do you want?";
D.q[1329] = "I\'m so pleased! Demons are not all idiots, I knew it! Always keep your honour! It could be an honourable war if everyone was acting like you do. Ok, I\'m going to shout from the rooftops. Clear off now!";
D.q[2748] = "You\'ll find the best fermented drinks on the island here. Forget anything you\'ve heard to the contrary... It\'s all lies. And let me give you some advice before you start knocking back the brew. If ever you need to drain the lizard, for Pandawa\'s sake, don\'t do it on the bamboo. If a guard sees you, your bladder will be the least of your worries.";
D.q[6485] = "Very funny. You\'ve got no business here, so go play monkey somewhere else until I give the signal. If I don\'t pay attention, someone could easily come along and steal the documents... and very likely hurt me too.";
D.q[3640] = "You\'re a smart little larva, aren\'t you? Yeah, you\'re a comedian, huh? Well listen to me. Until the day you earn my respect, you\'re nothing but a larva. You\'re the lowest form of life on Earth. You\'re not even human! Now get out of here before I really get mad.";
D.q[4881] = "Hmm, it\'s true... Ok, this is how we\'ll do it. Get stuck into that dirty little pig and then tell me you\'ve lost. I\'ll act as if it happened like that...";
D.q[2866] = "You\'re just in time to help me. Some militiamen have captured a soul and we have to find out what happened. It\'s going to be difficult to get him to talk, so we\'ll have to give him his body back. The trouble is that the usual method of resurrection doesn\'t work, and we don\'t know why. If you can manage to bring the soul back to life, you can be one of my apprentices.";
D.q[1418] = "Very good, I can go back to torturing Gnort Stonma.";
D.q[4268] = "We have to find a way to get in touch with Xephires and to corrupt him. I\'ll do some investigating on my side, and you can go ask the tavern keepers in Brakmar. Maybe they\'ll have heard about him.";
D.q[2803] = "You\'re about to enter the Village of Akwadala. Only those who have proven their strength can go through.";
D.q[2990] = "You\'ll be able to learn new emotions (also called emotes or smileys) when participating to quests. Go and see Wally Elconom in the Library of Amakna, he will offer you to do one of his quests.";
D.q[2397] = "You\'re now the apprentice under my supervision, don\'t disappoint me! To cut down trees, you\'ll need a good axe - you can buy one of mine for now, I\'ll give you a good price. Once you have it in your hands, pick a tree and start chopping like a nutter! One last thing, don\'t choose a hardwood tree. I\'ll write down where the softer trees are in your lumberjack\'s logbook , then you can practice on them.";
D.q[5042] = "Hello, I have another mission for you. As you surely know, there are many mines near Brakmar - Bonta has no such luck. We have to stop Brakmar taking control of these mines, and to do this, we\'re going to draw the best fighters they have away... Get over there now and visit them all. I want a full report when you return.";
D.q[730] = "I\'ve a perilous mission for you. You\'ll have to protect a farmer who works in the south of Amakna. The Bworks swarming over there are very likely to be hard on him.\n\nYou\'re in charge of his security. I hate being ominous. So, if he dies, YOU\'ll have to break the news to his family.";
D.q[4930] = "Hello, I was waiting... My men are preparing the camp as we speak. You\'re going to use this time to have a look around the Milicluster and the surrounding area. While you\'re there, ask the locals whether they\'ve seen many Brakmarians about.";
D.q[5004] = "Hello, do you know how difficult it\'s *hick* become to find a good marriage agency in Bonta?";
D.q[5499] = "Hello, you\'ll have to be quick, the other recruits need my help too, you know.";
D.q[5202] = "Hello, citizen of Bonta. What news do you have for me?";
D.q[6061] = "Hello. Come, come closer. Don\'t be afraid, I won\'t harm you. Did you come to see me or is it pure luck that has brought you here to me?";
D.q[4148] = "I don\'t know who you are, but let me tell you that I\'m one of the best bakers the World of Twelve has ever known. How upsetting to see that you don\'t seem to care, at all!\n\nHowever, you look a bit sly and spineless, you might be of some help.";
D.q[5347] = "Hello, you\'re looking for Divad? He went to the Misère Inn not so long ago. Me? I\'m just passing by, hehehe...";
D.q[2918] = "Hello. Any luck with the hunting?";
D.q[1301] = "There you are #1, come closer, people mustn\'t hear our conversation...\nWell, did you bring what I asked you for?";
D.q[6300] = "How many alchemists and miners have you led to death? Well, no matter. There\'s always plenty more to replace them. You can take your stones and go to the Well of Corrupted Souls. I don\'t know where the well is, but the master of the Order of the Unsound Mind should be able to tell you. When you find out where it is, go there with corruptah stones and bandit souls to perform the enslaving ceremony. If you accomplish your mission, I\'ll be very generous upon your return, believe me... well, probably anyway.";
D.q[6407] = "Cities? Places where thousands of people live together? What do you think I am, some kind of idiot? I know full well that such places don\'t exist. Beyond the Cania Plains there\'s the Cania Massif, then the Rocky Plains, then more plains, then nothing else.\nCities are a rumour started by the Kanigers to encourage people to all gather together in the same place. Why would they do that, you ask? Well, it means that the Kanigers don\'t have to strain to find their prey and they can have themselves a really good barbecue.\nYou\'ve got to be really thick to believe all that nonsense. I\'m way too smart to fall for it.";
D.q[4408] = "Did you find something from Brakmar?";
D.q[5047] = "Did you warn the Amaknean militia we were on our way?";
D.q[5109] = "Did you get all the souls I asked for?";
D.q[4706] = "Do you have my Rib Bones?";
D.q[4807] = "Thank *hic* you so much. I\'m so glad I can count on you *hic*. Go tell Amayiro that the trial can start *hic*.";
D.q[2691] = "Well, well, well... If you\'re here for the delivery, can you tell me why some of my order is missing? If you lost it on the way, it\'s your problem, not mine! I wanted 10 units of Bamboo wood, no less! And watch out, not everyone is as nice as I am!";
D.q[6162] = "As I\'ve already explained, I tried to get there myself long ago by sailing to this island in my ark with many creatures from the continent aboard. I failed, the plan was too ambitious. Now I\'ve decided to enlist the help of adventurers like you in the hopes that they can capture the souls of the creatures I require. This quest may well prove to be very dangerous, and so I\'m offering the greatest reward of all to adventurers who take up my offer. I\'ll give them a Dofus, and all the power that goes with these magical objects.";
D.q[4861] = "It\'s a pity you\'re so tied up in the trial, but the important thing is that Kit Dingaround got his job back.";
D.q[3921] = "Councillor Yse is very determined but doesn\'t seem well informed. He doesn\'t know how to injure the King ... AND, he\'s been unmasked! Neither him nor I\'ve time to get the information. You\'ll take care of this, alright? Here, take these Kamas to and prepare yourself.";
D.q[3680] = "Well if it isn\'t my little larva! You better watch your step. You\'ll not laugh, you\'ll not cry, you\'ll learn by the numbers I\'ll teach you!";
D.q[6547] = "You\'re a larva. Larvae are stupid, disciplined and they crawl before their master. From now on you\'ll do what I command. You\'ll forget any compassion you may have had and your greatest desire will be to work for the glory of Djaul and Brakmar. If you dare to show an ounce of morality or virtue, your body will be left to the Whitish Fangs and your brain will be fed to hungry Iops.\nNow, get out of my sight.";
D.q[4330] = "I\'m sorry but you\'re too weak to use this transportation... \nCome back when you\'re a bit stronger.";
D.q[1546] = "You\'re motivated. You have great ambitions and brilliant ideas... You\'ll never be short of Kamas.";
D.q[4828] = "It\'s all your fault I\'m here. For your sake, things better move quickly.";
D.q[5859] = "It\'s been ages! I suppose I should do something now?";
D.q[5419] = "Hello, are you here to take over?";
D.q[4297] = "I\'ve a feeling you\'re thirsty for some Brakmarian-style action. I\'m going to give you a mission that is sure to quench your thirst. \nMilone needs a Kain Dharyn crystal... these crystals are very rare and sought-after, in case you didn\'t know. My spies have reported that the family of Captain Starky of Bonta had a few. We simply can\'t attack Captain Starky directly. You\'re going to kidnap his niece, Sabine and demand the Kain Dharyn crystal in return. I\'ll mark where he lives on your map.";
D.q[163] = "Fantastic, you sure are lucky! You won, and it\'s been a while since it last happened in this tavern.\n\n(Grizmine gives you the Kamas, scratching his whiskers and purring)";
D.q[5785] = "Ahhhhh... *stretches* No harm in stealing a little bit, now is there? Who are you by the way, do we know each other?";
D.q[5445] = "";
D.q[5969] = "I\'m sorry, but I can\'t make a dishonoured person Neutral again. Come back and see me when you have restored your honour.";
D.q[6466] = "I\'m sorry, but I can\'t send any more men without the permission of the council. Did you manage to infiltrate the enemy\'s hideout?";
D.q[6168] = "I\'m sorry... I realise you\'re enthusiastic, but you\'re just not experienced enough to come and help me. I\'ll wait till you\'re a bit better travelled until I give you something to do.";
D.q[838] = "I\'m starting to lose my patience...";
D.q[4203] = "I\'m sure that you can get through this door...\nDid you know that it leads to the Bherb\'s Gully?\nIt\'s a very dangerous area, inhabited by Silf the Greater Bherb, a creature who is surprising and terrifying by turns.";
D.q[5786] = "Piwiwiwi.";
D.q[659] = "I can make you a wedding ring but I\'ll need 25 gold nuggets and 1,000 Kamas.";
D.q[3099] = "I\'m telling you, you\'ll find it. You\'re smart!";
D.q[5677] = "I\'m surrounded by imbeciles. I hope for your sake that you have the statues.";
D.q[617] = "His alibi was a bit weak but, all things considered, a real murderer would have found something more credible. That in itself was enough to get him off the hook.";
D.q[5798] = "I can\'t wait to blow that cursed tower up. Have you done what I\'ve asked?";
D.q[5102] = "Hey, what was that noise? What\'s going on here?";
D.q[5000] = "He, my friend. I\'m just back from the Castle of Amakna. All this business between Allister and his brother is so exhausting! So, are you going to buy me a beer or what?";
D.q[667] = "Metarias are spheres made of a highly magic-proof membrane which contains a liquid compound with magical properties. I discovered them by chance during a joust with a Dreggon. After some research, I manage to fathom the mystery.";
D.q[4614] = "Hey! Who are you? Answer me before I run you through!";
D.q[4651] = "Thank you for your help. I should be fine now.";
D.q[5840] = "Hey, you\'re back. I didn\'t think I\'d be seeing you so soon. Can I get you a beer?";
D.q[690] = "These famous worn boots are really in a sorry state. But a very skilful shoemaker should be able to give them back their original powers and their unique character.";
D.q[4378] = "You\'ll regret it, believe me.";
D.q[6266] = "Here\'s a Kain Dharyn Crystal. Give my niece and it\'s yours.";
D.q[1272] = "I\'m the chief cook of the militia, now get out of my kitchen!";
D.q[3272] = "I\'m the dungeon keeper and this dungeon contains a part of the inhabitants of this forest. I can come with you if you wish, but I\'ll stay far behind since I don\'t run as fast as you with my worn roots. \nIf you want to get in, give me the key to this dungeon.";
D.q[694] = "To you, I want to pay homage.\nYou got the message!\nNothing in love is determined,\nTo each one to chose his destiny...";
D.q[6296] = "I\'m the guardian of the Well of the Corrupted Souls. You\'ve beaten me. That means you can make one request, any request. Choose wisely.";
D.q[5060] = "Hmm. The agency sent me here to negociate with the Wabbits... so that they don\'t attack everyone who comes here on sight, but they\'re totally paranoid that everyone who comes here wants to steal their Cawwots... well, that\'s what they told me when I asked them. It\'s completely unweasonable... sorry, unreasonable.";
D.q[735] = "Today\'s your lucky day my friend! You\'re on spud-bashing duty!\nYou get out of it until now but this time you won\'t.\nBring 200 pods of peeled spuds to the cook!";
D.q[2568] = "I\'m very busy taking care of those sick Enutrofs... All this isn\'t a good sign...";
D.q[3876] = "I\'m tired of all these adventures. I think I\'ll rest for a while...";
D.q[5826] = "Let me have a guess. You\'ll here to waste my time again, is that it?";
D.q[5831] = "Wooo... Me find Bontawian. Me get weally special mission. Me say nothing about weally special mission";
D.q[1469] = "I\'m very sorry, I can\'t talk to you. I\'m on patrol.";
D.q[4679] = "Ah, finally I\'ve found what I need to replace my grotty old spear.";
D.q[6596] = "I\'m very busy, I really don\'t have the time to explain anything. What I can do is sell you a plan for 500 Kamas. Another handyman can then make what you need. What do you think?";
D.q[3117] = "I\'m very impressed, little one! You defeated my pets.\nYou\'re worth me trying to bring you back to life.\nI\'ll exchange you a resurrection powder and your ghost body for a resurrection, but it will only be effective once you get out of here. Then, you\'ll be with your master again.";
D.q[5833] = "Greetings. The Tower of Gisgoul is still standing. I\'d like you to explain that to me. Well?";
D.q[4611] = "Reveal to you the place I will. North-east all the way on the island you will go. Find you will a statue. Search you will. Find the horn you will.";
D.q[6312] = "I\'m very tempted *hic*, but I\'m on duty for the next twenty-four hours. It seems I\'m drinking at work too... *hic*... can you believe that!?";
D.q[4961] = "Hmm, you\'d have to find a very stupid race that would believe in any old half-baked lies... Wabbits. Wabbits are what you\'re looking for. They\'d be perfect for that. Don\'t bother going to Wa, he\'s a little less confused that most of his people. You\'ll have no trouble finding a Wabbit to fool.";
D.q[815] = "I\'ve a funny mission to offer you... to extract Gobball teeth.\nTalk to Boud Chair the butcher, he will tell you how to go about it.\nOnce you have enough teeth to make a set of dentures, bring them back to me. I\'ll use them to patch up a useless twit I know.\nDon\'t bring too many teeth! It\'s good to have fun now and then but you have to know when to stop! And do as I say, or else...";
D.q[929] = "Huh? You\'ve already defeated Torch? You\'re alright for a new guy... Unfortunately, you\'ll remain a scrawny little scaraleaf for a while yet in my eyes.\nFeel free to come back whenever you want.";
D.q[6553] = "I\'ve been forging the Bontarian militia\'s equipment for the past few months and it\'s a lot more tiring than I thought it would be, especially since Two-fingers swapped the forge for the marketplace. I\'ve really started to wonder if I chose the right job... even my Tofus are useless. As a matter of fact, I only keep doing the job to keep my father happy. He had to pull some strings with his relations in Bonta to get me it.";
D.q[3509] = "I\'ve already tried but he was so dirty that I had to throw him in a pit where he was fed with Goblins. I\'ve got another idea and you can help me pull it off.";
D.q[3861] = "I\'ve been told that you\'ve been given a task for your profession. You should really get on with it.\n";
D.q[5835] = "You\'re in luck, I\'m not too busy at the moment. What did you want to tell me?";
D.q[4406] = "Hmmm, now you\'re talking. So here\'s the inside story. One of Oto Mustam\'s little wingmen, the head of the militia, has managed to bribe one of your men. No, it\'s not that Xartruc fellow. I was asked to make a jewel beautiful enough to entice your man, and there will be a meeting soon enough at the Tower of Bonta to seal the deal. Ok, that\'s all I\'ve got for you, now scram.";
D.q[4385] = "How did the trip go?";
D.q[924] = "Hello sweetheart! Did Amayiro send you? I wish he\'d come down here in person. Anyway darlin\', it doesn\'t matter, just give him this letter from me, will ya? It contains the name of the filthy pig who harasses me and my girls...";
D.q[1066] = "I see, you want to out the militiaman who don\'t take their breaks? Very well! I\'d have done it but I\'m bone idle. I can\'t tell you the ones who don\'t have their breaks but I can tell you that Brank Thoof, Haco Norss, Jack Rottance and Kad Maxy are always around. I\'ll write the names down for you...";
D.q[5381] = "How could you leave me rot like this. Get out of here!";
D.q[5886] = "Tell me how your search is going? Have you found Maimane?";
D.q[1128] = "Bad day for Tofu hunting!";
D.q[4175] = "I\'ve dreamt of something better than Scaraleaves for years now. I wish I could try a Dragoturkeys... They\'re faster, more docile and seem more intelligent than my Scaraleaves. If you bring me back a certificate for a Ginger Dragoturkey and one for an Almond Dragoturkey, I\'ll let you use my Scarplane as much as you like!";
D.q[4675] = "Very tired I am, some sleep I need. Yes, sleep lots of I need.";
D.q[4339] = "I accept your conditions. Don\'t stay here, you could be ambushed.";
D.q[1502] = "Here, a set of gold dentures - an exact replica of the ones Elite Chafers wear.";
D.q[2652] = "Wisdom makes you talk, or perhaps it\'s stupidity. Indeed, this art has a certain weakness which is quite a strength at the same time. The Pandasiman art has been developed to limit losses during Pandawaiian wars. All our shields and parries are developed to face particular types of opponents, in particular types of fights.";
D.q[1506] = "No time anyway... I can see a wave of enemies approaching. Get ready! CHAFER HOLD ON THE BOWS! TAKE AIM...";
D.q[5129] = "I\'ll be at the Tower of Gisgoul soon.";
D.q[4680] = "A create of equipment? Yeah, that can always come in handy.";
D.q[1533] = "Hummm, you do know how to talk to innkeepers. The code for this house is 11115555.\nAt night, Ufot organises bets on Tofu fighting, not very legal in my opinion...";
D.q[3656] = "I\'ve got a mission for you... if you think you\'re up to it!";
D.q[822] = "I\'ve got a message to pass on to Vil Smisse at the Amakna cemetery.";
D.q[5116] = "Hello, I\'m very busy at the moment. I\'m working on an invincibility potion. If people keep bothering me all the time, I\'ll never get it finished.";
D.q[1598] = "Oh, I see you\'ve reached the second level. Congratulations!";
D.q[1600] = "Do you have the 3 items I asked you for? Fine! Equip them and you\'ll be able to pass to the next room";
D.q[6961] = "If I were to sell my boars any cheaper than that it would be insulting to them. Although... I have this one obese boar that\'s covered in ticks. It\'s breath is worse than a bworkette\'s armpits who has spent the night dancing. I can\'t sell it, no sensible person would want to buy it. You can have it for 1,000 Kamas. Buy now, no refunds, please check your change before leaving the store.";
D.q[2356] = "I got these Vhan seeds off the dark Rose of the Astrub fields... Wanna see some sparks fly... well, plant them under that rock over there and run back to me as fast as you can... Hihihiiii!";
D.q[5466] = "... and pecan nut!";
D.q[5181] = "I was sick and tired of being trapped in those underground tunnels. Finally the carnage can continue!";
D.q[2182] = "Thank you. Please, wait here. It won\'t take too long... There you go, give this potion to Yol. He should be able to wake Locette up.";
D.q[2334] = "You really think I\'m afraid of that scoundrel! I\'m gonna beat him to a pulp! Get out of here if you\'re frightened, you\'ll only get in my way! I\'ve to deliver this beer... and you better not try to stop me!";
D.q[6704] = "I\'m surprised that my uncle came to pay the ransom. I\'d have preferred it if he came to kick your butts instead.";
D.q[5669] = "I\'ve heard about these traitors. They went into hiding in a house in the Porco Territory. Just so you know, there are three of them and they\'re not afraid of a good punch up, so watch out. If I were you I\'d go look for some backup first.";
D.q[1818] = "I need some wrappings to redo my mummification, I think Ouginaks use it and I\'m sure you could get me some in exchange of a fight against a Dopple!";
D.q[1611] = "(ne pas traduire)";
D.q[6361] = "I\'ve heard about this boat. It belonged to the city of Bonta and was used to transport important goods, but that\'s all I know about it. I\'m really sorry I can\'t help you any better.";
D.q[145] = "(Grizmine puts the die in the Bronze tankard, moves the tankards around very quickly, and the die seems to pass from one tankard to another but there\'s no logical explanation for it)\n\nSo which tankard is the die in, my friend ?";
D.q[1615] = "(ne pas traduire)";
D.q[5769] = "I\'ve heard about you. They say you\'re no small fish! And that\'s why it\'ll cost you 16,000 Kamas to go neutral.\nAnd don\'t forget, you can join the weaker alignment for free!";
D.q[2345] = "*Deudoine gets two fingers out of his pocket, catches the iron pieces one by one, and with unbelievable strength he assembles them while his two other fingers strike the iron like a hammer* \nHere are your scissors, say hi to Resserd for me!";
D.q[4415] = "I\'m going, I\'m going! My accomplice!? He probably took advantage of the fight to take off.";
D.q[3738] = "Amaknean Resource Protectors sometimes attack harvesters. However, if you manage to defeat them, their riches will be all yours! ";
D.q[819] = "I\'ve heard that some of my soldiers never drink at the Inn during their duty. \nFind me the names of all the idiots who never have breaks!";
D.q[4869] = "Ah, fishing... there\'s nothing better if you want to just chill out.";
D.q[4870] = "A letter for me? Ah, I\'m late, it\'s true... but I really don\'t want to go there.";
D.q[5121] = "I\'m going to the Tower of Gisgoul very soon.";
D.q[5119] = "I\'m going to the Tower of Gisgoul soon.";
D.q[5064] = "I\'m going to the Tower of Gisgoul righ this minute.";
D.q[625] = "Ah! Uba Tesse sent you. I see, I see. Hum, if you came up all the way to meet me I guess you\'re quite motivated to become an alchemist. Unfortunately I\'m very busy right now. Here is what I propose, go and see a friend of mine, he\'s doing a pilgrimage for studies from temple to temple towards the south of Amakna. \nAt present, he\'s probably stopped in a tiny village as he\'s done half of his trip.";
D.q[5058] = "At least they won\'t die of hunger. But they keep on digging and even my cultured Wabbit spirit can\'t make them stop. I want you to find an interpreter to translate my orders. You might find one on Wabbit Island.";
D.q[3700] = "Ah? A profession. Well, that\'s easy. This time it\'ll be free, but let me tell you, they won\'t be so generous in Amakna. Potions that allow you to forget a profession might be common, but they\'re not free. Anyway, let\'s get started!";
D.q[3004] = "Ask for my scrolls! They\'re illuminated and warranted without any spelling mistakes! I also have elemental scrolls, the best you\'ll find in the whole region. May you want to check it for yourself, here are the addresses of my competitors!";
D.q[5189] = "I was lucky the case was dismissed. You had a part to play in that, thank you.";
D.q[2025] = "Just take a look at that carved wooden shaft! Isn\'t it great work ?!";
D.q[6565] = "Bark.";
D.q[2037] = "Ah! Another young Iop I presume? Sure, I can explain to you how to make this weapon, but we\'ll need something to make the handle first. Go and ask Oli Venders, he must have a couple in stock, ha-ha! I\'m starting to beat the iron, so don\'t dawdle.";
D.q[3544] = "Aha! A Sadida. Will you persevere, young one? A mastery of the creation of living things awaits your soft, shaking hands. You\'ll achieve great things. I need someone like you right now. Use your powers to summon a band of dolls... then kill the parasites infesting the region.";
D.q[3451] = "Whoa! A mate! Apparently you won\'t stay here too long.\nSee the door right there? It leads outside. Whoa? No no, I\'d rather stay here. That\'s nice because we\'ve board and lodging, we are protected from the rain... Whoa? If I can pass through the door? IF I CAN PASS THROUGH THE DOOR? You want me to eat your arm? OF COURSE I can. I just DON\'T want to. And stop looking at me with those mocking eyes! WHOOOOA!";
D.q[2943] = "I\'ve lost my pet in this dark cave and I\'m scared to go inside all by myself. Lots of adventurers tried to go get it but all those who had a group of less than seven adventurers never came back. Are you sure you want to go inside the cave?";
D.q[4872] = "My delivery is late again... this is going to create problems.";
D.q[6453] = "I\'ve never had the slightest problem with my customers. Sometimes they have problems with me! Ecaline on the other hand tends to attract the loutish types... like your friends there. You should go ask him.";
D.q[1961] = "What do you want? Oh, are you the one who beat up that idiot Kaba? Pah, and you waltz in here like butter wouldn\'t melt! You must have some kind of death wish!";
D.q[4871] = "You\'d do that for me!? Thank you! I\'m going to write a letter for the tavern keeper pretending I\'m sick. Then you can replace me.";
D.q[833] = "I\'ve put some money aside, but it\'s still not enough. Ok, a new military tax has just been introduced. It must be paid from today on by all Inns. And you, my new tax collector, you\'ll claim it for me.";
D.q[5962] = "I\'ve rarely seen Jiva so enraged, this assembly should be a lot of fun!";
D.q[4641] = "I\'ve thought a lot about it. Tell your boss that I\'ll accept his conditions. My loyalty to Brakmar in exchange for the jewel once I\'d completed the mission.";
D.q[3647] = "Ahhh! I knew this story would interest you. Let\'s start from the start. Years ago, I was venturing in the Pandawaïan badlands when I suddenly started to cough. I couldn\'t stop and I thought I had caught some kind of... but then I kicked a piece of grass and there was a stone right under my foot, so I used the stone to make some pea soup...";
D.q[4875] = "Stolen. Guards? Prisoner? Rob. KILL.";
D.q[1742] = "Enutrofs are usually very fortunate characters but they\'re always looking for things to help them get luckier.";
D.q[5894] = "I heard our Bontarian contact is dead. Did you manage to get the fake document from Maimane?";
D.q[2470] = "Thank you for your help. I hope you\'ll accept my modest reward... here, take this rune.";
D.q[6185] = "I\'m very busy at the moment, my job as chief of the militia is not too easy. I might have some time for you later on.";
D.q[5555] = "I\'m very busy at the moment. How do you expect me to finish my Invincibility Potion if you don\'t leave me in peace?";
D.q[5225] = "I get the feeling you\'ve come here with bad news!";
D.q[6187] = "I need you to be fit for battle before I give you your next mission. Come back to see me when you\'ve progressed";
D.q[5190] = "I don\'t need anything from you right now. \nGo back and see the chief of your militia.";
D.q[3868] = "Considering all that happened, the King wants to keep an eye on the Rogues... But you\'ve got to find them first! Their den is well-hidden... The only clue we have is that an important Sram is a member. You must find him. Can you help your King?";
D.q[1762] = "Make sure you\'re ready before you go fighting a Dopple. So, are you all set?";
D.q[2459] = "In the course of your adventure, you\'ll experience many exciting things. All these missions will be written down in your questbook. Can you see this old book down there? It will help your compass work. You should always keep an eye on it. It\'s going to be more than a guide for you, it will be a true testimony of your progression.";
D.q[5671] = "I\'ve nothing to tell you. Be on your way or I\'ll have to get rough.";
D.q[1768] = "I\'ve trained some Dopples to fight like Eniripsas. They make good training adversaries no matter what your level is.";
D.q[4526] = "Hurry up. Danathor doesn\'t like waiting.";
D.q[2176] = "Hello. Mmh, do you know I\'m quite famous round here? You must have seen my portrait somewhere. Think hard, I\'m sure you\'ve seen it.";
D.q[1137] = "I\'ve my doubts about the effectiveness of this venom. Would you mind tasting it to prove to me that it\'s not Blop juice?\nWhat do you mean you don\'t want to die? You young recruits have no respect for their superiors anymore. Clear off!";
D.q[1771] = "I\'ve trained some Dopples to fight like Iops. They make good training adversaries no matter what your level is.";
D.q[1999] = "Not at all. I\'ll go prepare the essence immediately! Humm? Two flasks of it? You also need some for Touh the Sadida, don\'t you? Alright, that\'s perfect. Anyway, I always have spare ones...Take them and good luck!";
D.q[5112] = "I never have enough disciples. Keep looking.";
D.q[3057] = "Allister\'s Castle is far from being completed. There are lots of details to finish off. I\'ll need some resources to finish building the royal residence. First bring me some planks.";
D.q[5891] = "I hope this plan will secure our victory over Bonta.";
D.q[1995] = "zzz\n*Locette is still sound asleep, but at least she looks alive*";
D.q[5601] = "I hope you\'ve come with good news on your lips.";
D.q[7036] = "I can exchange these coins against many different items, by way of thanks for your numerous victories. Do you need characteristic scrolls, for example, or spiritual gems containing the trapped souls of monsters? What do you need?";
D.q[3037] = "By Ecaflip, are you the new recruit?! I don\'t have time to check anyway. The priest in Astrub asked me to meet him and I need someone to reinforce the watch over these rogues. Will you join us? I\'ll reward you if you do!";
D.q[5869] = "Me keep tower safe. People come in me smash. You try come, me smash you and friends.";
D.q[2194] = "Here is a masterpiece... You just have to find someone who knows how to install the cord. Dear Setsinbol will be alright but everyone knows that his son Ticra is the best.";
D.q[3369] = "This is what you\'ll have to do. Go see the Key Master, he will entrust you with a mission. Should you be lucky enough to satisfy his demanding trials, I\'ll personally give you our family relic. There is no artefact as powerful in the World of Twelve.";
D.q[5660] = "...\nCan\'t you see you\'re disturbing me, no?";
D.q[1314] = "zzzZZZzzz";
D.q[1962] = "An explanation? You\'re not in any position to ask for an explanation, mate.";
D.q[2434] = "You\'ll have to take a small detour, he\'s on the peninsula at the centre of the lake.";
D.q[7132] = "Make sure you\'re ready before you go fighting a Dopple. So, are you all set?";
D.q[6057] = "I must find a way to seduce her... Hey, are you there? Hello, what can I do for you?";
D.q[4809] = "Pnj(180) et Message(4808)";
D.q[5287] = "Pnj(305) et Message(5284)";
D.q[6710] = "I suppose that if I release it into these cultures, I\'ll prove to Raymon Santho that I\'m a loyal follower... and he\'ll pay me for my services.";
D.q[2722] = "Everyone says those paths are twisting and the creatures that haunt them are not what you\'d call friendly. But a fellow by the name of Wally Elconom succeeded in drawing a map. It could be useful for you to meet him. He\'s often to be seen round Amakna.";
D.q[5533] = "Hey there cutie, welcome to Bagrutte\'s Inn!";
D.q[6963] = "I\'ve trained some Dopples to fight like Pandawas. They make good training adversaries no matter what your level is.";
D.q[2081] = "It\'s easy, Ma Cleopatra has developed a cure. I need somebody to go fetch it, and quickly. She\'s a very skilled healer, is Ma Cleopatra. Can I count on you?";
D.q[2654] = "The easiest way to learn is to get a shield and fight! Our shields are especially designed to favour instinctive parrying movement. This way, we gain time to train newcomers. This basic move is called the Pandasiman-Screen: it\'s the essence of our art. Then you have more and more complex sequences which only masters can perform.";
D.q[3638] = "All clear!? We\'re gonna end up rotting in this hole!";
D.q[1481] = "Hmm, you\'ve got too many things on your mind for the moment. You can\'t learn everything at once. Come back when you\'re not so busy and you\'ve mastered your other professions better.";
D.q[1293] = "Hem, a red creature that spits fire and walks upright on two feet?\nThe only Brakmarian creature it could be is the Holbaïd. Take this letter and give it to Amayiro. I wrote down how to defeat this demon....";
D.q[1799] = "I\'ve trained some Dopples to fight like Sacrier. They make good training adversaries no matter what your level is.";
D.q[4738] = "I know about the hammer. I can make the hammer\'s Spirit of Light leave the hammer, but it has to be beaten to make sure it never comes back.";
D.q[98] = "I\'m Rigal Hookhand. Everybody here respects me because they all know that I\'m one of the Rogues...";
D.q[5624] = "...";
D.q[3038] = "By Ecaflip, are you the new recruit?! I don\'t have time to check anyway. The priest in Astrub asked me to meet him and I need someone to reinforce the watch over these rogues. Will you join us? I\'ll reward you if you do!";
D.q[7452] = "";
D.q[4999] = "I don\'t want to spend all day on introductions, but anyway, I am As\'Ruoy\'Dni, guru of the temple dedicated to Rushu. I reduced Ankama to ruins under my boot not so long ago, but a horrible twist of fate tore it all out of my hands.";
D.q[2168] = "Good morning dear client! What can I do for you today? I sell a lot of different things: preservatives, preparations for nyfish, meat, yeast, fruits and vegetables. You only need one word here, buddy... BUY! I\'ll also buy back some of your items if you want...";
D.q[1837] = "Welcome young adventurer. I\'m ready to sell you the equipment and even a few apples if You\'re ready to give me some Kamas. Good luck for the tournament.";
D.q[7453] = "";
D.q[7454] = "";
D.q[5741] = "...";
D.q[3031] = "Here, take this book! This manual will tell you how to become a perfect Bontarian initiate! Then, go and meet Amayiro, the chief of the Militia. Only he can decide whether to hire you... or to kick your hands off, as he\'s fond of saying!";
D.q[1770] = "I\'ve trained some Dopples to fight like Sadidas. They make good training adversaries no matter what your level is.";
D.q[449] = "If the hammer doesn\'t interest you, you can give me Gobball Horns, and I\'ll give you a Small Wisdom Scroll in return. You\'ll need 100 horns per scroll.";
D.q[3067] = "She still refuses? She wants me to go over there? Allister will never let me leave the building site of the castle for such trivialities. Well, try with Wartella, she\'s at the harbour of Allister\'s Castle. Tell me when she\'s available.";
D.q[1807] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Enutrof temple.\nIt will cost you one unit of Ebonite.";
D.q[7455] = "";
D.q[1822] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Iop temple.\nIt will cost you a Bakelelite.";
D.q[7456] = "";
D.q[3104] = "It sounds wonderful. I\'ll be able to work on my complexion. However it is quite far away. Bring me back a tame Dragoturkey. Don\'t forget to get some sunflower oil as well so I can anoint my delicate body. Thank you, darling.";
D.q[1823] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Iop temple.\nIt will cost you a Major Arachnee leg.";
D.q[4983] = "IIIIDDDDDDDIIIIIOOOOOOTTTTTT!!! What? You want to kill me too? Well I think it\'s too late for that... a Bontarian is on the case! The medallion? He took it, obviously. I think he went north of here. I gave him one before I kicked the bucket so he won\'t be going anywhere quick... you should be able to catch him...";
D.q[4383] = "Is it time?";
D.q[1787] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Osamodas temple.\nIt will cost you a Boar tusk.";
D.q[7457] = "";
D.q[1830] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Sadida temple.\nIt will cost you a Hazel.";
D.q[1780] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Feca temple.\nIt will cost you a Gobball Horn.";
D.q[5295] = "";
D.q[3177] = "Haha! You have no class honey. Compared to me, you look like a ninny and so much not like a Koolich! Haha, you\'re so ugly! Yuk! At least, I wear Moowolf. Yes, dear, Moowolf.... It\'s very different from what you mama wears... what is it already? Gobball? How gross... Anyway. Do you want to get in this cave? Yes or no? Adventurers used to breed their Bow Wows in here but no one knows what happened. Now, it\'s infested with terrible creatures. I believe they\'ll kill you easily. But be careful Gobbly! I won\'t come get you if you\'re in trouble! Even if I hear you cry like a girl!";
D.q[6502] = "If Amayiro thinks you need help, you can count on me. I\'m leaving for the castle this instant.";
D.q[5250] = "You\'re presence here is annoying me more by the day. Tell me quickly what you want.";
D.q[1782] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Feca temple.\nIt will cost you a Gobball War Chief horn.";
D.q[1783] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Feca temple.\nIt will cost you Gobball wool.";
D.q[2004] = "If Dad don\'t see you near me, he\'s gonna be cross!";
D.q[6774] = "";
D.q[5779] = "If I had they choice, I would never grow old. When I see all the worries and bother these adults have, it makes me happy to know that I have a few years of childhood left in me yet.";
D.q[1954] = "Well... okay. You seem like an honest person. I\'ll follow you... But don\'t get in my way, or you\'ll be sorry!";
D.q[2110] = "Thank you so much! You\'re doing us a great favour.";
D.q[6775] = "";
D.q[3237] = "That big hole you see there will take you to what we call the Dreggon Sanctuary. We know very little about this mysterious place where different Dreggon species have been living for ages. Many adventurers tried to get in and penetrate the secrets of this sanctuary, but very few actually came back. What we do know, is that this sanctuary was built long ago by Osamodas\' disciples to protect and make mating easier for his Dragons.";
D.q[1087] = "Thanks. I didn\'t think you\'d bring these weapons so quickly. They will come in very handy for us!";
D.q[3241] = "When Osamodas decided to free the Dreggons, they attacked the village and its residents. They popped out of the ground, smashing open house floors and breaking the most solid slabs. This attack surprised all the inhabitants leaving them no chance to counterattack. Nature has reclaimed her rights and the village is a mere shadow of what it used to be... But the ruins seem to be resisting the throes of time as if Osamodas had wanted to convey a message and engrave it in our memories to warn future generations.";
D.q[6776] = "";
D.q[2447] = "Life is hard down here. If a creature finishes off your vitality, you\'ll be shattered. You\'ll have to sit down somewhere to recover from your wounds. If it\'s more serious, eat some bread, which you can buy from a baker, or drink a healing potion - some alchemists make excellent ones. After that, you can make the most out of life.";
D.q[5552] = "Greetings. Have you found a way to make cereals grow quicker?";
D.q[3682] = "Have I noticed anything out of the ordinary? No, nothing\'s wrong, I didn\'t notice anything unusual. Apart maybe some broken Zaaps, and the overexcited guards, not that it would matter here anyway.";
D.q[285] = "What ho, chap! I say! My name is Cholmondeley Featherstonehaugh. I come from the Land of Eng, and I\'d like nothing more than to bally well open a spiffing top-hole restaurant, what what? I say! My speciality is wild Gobball leg with mint sauce, served with a pint of warm, flat ale. I say! What what? Yoinks!\nHmm... I say! That sounds delicious, doesn\'t it? Rather!\nI say. But, I need mint jelly, and I\'m bally well stuck here watching over the flat ale. What rotten luck, no? I\'d say!\n";
D.q[3767] = "Creatures are easy to come by around here. Do your best to kill them off quick. If you need some help, you can always ask around.";
D.q[2483] = "Thanks! We can go back to work now, thank you... (he yawns)";
D.q[1540] = "Thank you! You saved me! I can cook my feast now. Take this roasted Gobball leg by way of thanks.";
D.q[4382] = "Thanks. Tell me when the convoy can leave. You\'ll be joining the escort, by the way.";
D.q[3786] = "Hello my friend... It\'s your lucky day, roll up, roll up... I\'m offering you the one-time chance of a lifetime... but, let\'s not dwell on life... I\'m talking about the other side, the dark side of the moon, the third side of the coin... how about it? Trust me, everything\'s under control!";
D.q[3523] = "If goblin become magus, goblin not be Bwork slave anymore!";
D.q[7459] = "";
D.q[7460] = "";
D.q[2102] = "I understand. In that case, I\'m sorry for you. If you change your mind, you know where to find me.";
D.q[5214] = "";
D.q[4321] = "Hmm, It really was worth coming on time if all it gets you is a beating from a bunch of thieving losers like these. \nLuckily the one I had on me was a fake.\nGo back to your chief and tell him I\'ll be finished soon, but the next time I want him to send someone who knows how to fight!\nOne of the thieves dropped this piece of paper during the fight. You\'ll need to clean up the militia to make sure this kind of thing doesn\'t happen again.";
D.q[2609] = "So, I hope you\'re enjoying your stay at the fire-eaters!\nSo there was another magic totem? I\'m beginning to understand... this old legend... about Maimane...\nAnyway, my assistant doesn\'t need to know any more about this.\n\nBe careful! There\'s a picture of a Bwork on this page... and it doesn\'t look very friendly... Go to their villages, there must be an entrance somewhere!";
D.q[4953] = "Do you have the information I requested, you little creep? My patience has its limits, you know. And you\'re walking a thin line on that limit... of my patience.";
D.q[6289] = "Hahahahaha!\nMwahhaha!\nA priceless jewel you say? Let me guess... someone stole it off you and you\'re looking for the thieves? \nHahahahaha!\nI don\'t sell my associates out just like that. Who do you take me for?\nMwahhaha!";
D.q[2032] = "Here are the facts: The Enutrofs asked for our help since strange things have been happening during their excavations lately. It\'s not safe, and not safe means lop! You\'re now prepared to assist them. Meet the excavation team in the galleries! And stay on your guard...";
D.q[956] = "If like me you\'ve had enough of this segregation that haunts our city, where the rich are kept to one side and the other rich kept to the other... If you like me truly believe in the ideals of inequality... then join my group.";
D.q[1775] = "You don\'t have enough Kamas to buy these scissors.";
D.q[3086] = "She doesn\'t want it anymore? What a heifer! Try Haraquiri, the King\'s butcher. I think he\'d like to get in the King\'s good books to increase his orders. Well, hurry up and bring him the potion... and bring me back the Kamas. Don\'t worry, you\'ll get your share. If you\'re late, I\'m telling you, you\'ll try my patience.";
D.q[4984] = "So have you got the support of the council?";
D.q[4366] = "Hmm, so you gave the bandits a good beating and you even went as far as risking you life to get into their hideout. I admire your courage, but I need people with sense too. It\'s a pity you didn\'t get any further into their hideout. \nI wanted to raise a troop to go along with you, but the counsel didn\'t agree with me. With the new information you brought me I hope they\'ll change their minds. \n\nHere\'s a few potions for your injuries. Get some rest and come back to see me when you\'ve recovered.";
D.q[3880] = "Eh? What are you doing here? What? Hire me? I tell you, kid, my services are expensive and that I don\'t offer them to anyone.";
D.q[4724] = "You have what you want, now leave me alone!";
D.q[5411] = "Hello, you look like you have something on your mind... what do you need?";
D.q[5848] = "Hello, it\'s good to see you. How can I help you?";
D.q[4106] = "The second potion allows you to reset your characteristics to 101, if you don\'t want to lose anything you\'ve gained through scrolls.\nIf you use it, any characteristic above the value 101 will be reset to 101, and you\'ll get back the appropriate number of characteristic points. A characteristic below the value 101 will not be affected.";
D.q[3600] = "You\'re patient, aren\'t you? Well, you\'ll become patient if you practice some more. It\'s an extremely useful profession to feed yourself while relaxing. Do you want a fishing rod and some advice to start with?";
D.q[1758] = "Xelors hate to waste time, that\'s why it\'s hard to find an experienced Xelor to train with. So I\'ve trained some Dopples to fight like us, they will make good training adversaries no matter what your level is.";
D.q[1743] = "Cras are often very nimble characters, and sometimes strong or intelligent. They wear equipment that can make them more limber, strong and intelligent.";
D.q[4138] = "Hello! I\'m Professor Kalkulus.\nSince I lost my seven balls, I\'ve been healing the wounded creatures of this island. Sometimes, I just have to finish them off. \nI always wanted to help living beings and put an end to their suffering. It became a genuine passion. If you have some time to dedicate me, I may need your help.";
D.q[4325] = "Hmm, what can I get you? A beer, no doubt?";
D.q[2072] = "Hurrywood... It\'s become pretty rare around here , boy oh boy, so rare that the only people who can ever get their hands on some are the Enutrofs. And I\'m not even sure if they have any! I can make something that\'s close to it - I\'ve very similar woods!";
D.q[4364] = "If those bandits come all the way over here, we\'ll have to start taking defensive measures.";
D.q[3922] = "Well, go to the castle, ask every single royal servant, search every nook... don\'t worry about the crannies too much... Oh blast! Can\'t you do anything for yourself?";
D.q[5589] = "You look tired. Have you revived Terra Bitya?";
D.q[4296] = "I sent men to find the less rare materials. You I\'m keeping for the difficult tasks. I want five ingots of gold and some mother of pearl. You probably don\'t know where to find mother of pearl, but that\'s no surprise - that\'s why I\'m the boss. \nGet 10 unworked mothers of pearl off the crustaceans and molluscs on Otomai Island... you might try the Craborals and the Coralators. Then you\'ll need a miner to polish them.\nBring me some Royal Gobball Slobber too... and don\'t ask me why, I\'ll tell you when you need to know. And most importantly, never forget who gives the orders around here. \nWhat are you doing? Scram! Get to work!";
D.q[6068] = "I am very busy at the moment, but I\'ll tell you a good one if I get a few moments.";
